## -------------------- The Length Function ------------------------- ##

# len() is used to represent the length funtion
## this function tells how long a string, list or other data type is
### the length function returns an integer value

print(len(input("What is your name")))

# the above example will execute thusly:

    "What is your name?"
    User: Dan
    Return: 3

# my name is Dan, dan has 3 characters, thus, the computer returns the integer 3

# integers (int) are another data type
## they are represented by a whole number, without quotation marks, and no remainder or decimal
